HEADWORD: Electro-metallurgy
<hw>E*lec`tro-met"al*lur`gy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The
act or art precipitating a metal electro-chemical action, by which a
coating is deposited, on a prepared surface, as in electroplating and
electrotyping; galvanoplasty.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

